{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"DESIGN DECISIONS + DERISK RESULTS (brainstorm + experiment spike, 2026-06-28)\n\nDecomposed into 7 child stories S1-S7 (depends_on chain: S1<-S2<-S3<-{S4,S5}; S5<-S6; {S4,S5,S6}<-S7). S1 is the ready entry point.\n\n== DECISIONS LOCKED (this brainstorm) ==\n- Posture: a LIVE proof-of-concept that runs ALL proposed code-review mechanisms and gates EVERY commit to rebar `main`, with few developers. Priorities, in order: (1) function + certified integrity on all commits to main [non-negotiable]; (2) decreased cost within AWS; (3) reliability/restore-speed/reusability ONLY if it doesn't hurt (1) or (2).\n- Outage posture: FREEZE-AND-RESTORE, no break-glass in v1. If Gerrit/MCP/LLM is down, `main` is unmergeable until restored; engineering goes into fast rebuild-from-IaC + monitoring, not a bypass. Justified because GitHub mirrors all MERGED code (only in-flight reviews are at risk on a crash -> RPO acceptable; RTO via IaC).\n- Hosting: AWS (account 896586841071, us-east-1) — justified by the existing company account + the flexibility to co-host the rebar MCP + avoiding not-worth-it IT approval. Cost-lean: single Graviton t4g.large, default VPC, NO ALB/NAT, gp3, SSM Parameter Store (free) over Secrets Manager, on-box nginx+Let's Encrypt.\n- Reverse proxy = nginx+certbot, NOT Caddy (Caddy URL-decodes %2F by default; Gerrit needs encoded-slash preservation). One real change from the first sketch.\n- Review bot = EXTERNAL bot (the existing rebar MCP) driving Gerrit's Set Review REST endpoint — not an in-process Java plugin (prior art: amarula/reviewai + official plugins/ai-code-review for the voting model; we use the external shape since the MCP already runs the kernel).\n- Replication = core Apache-2.0 `replication` plugin (push), non-force, mirror=false, replicatePermissions=false. The GerritForge BSL re-license (2025-09-30) touches only pull-replication/multi-site, not this.\n- GitHub lockdown = REPO-LEVEL ruleset (navapbc is a `free` org -> admin-proof ORG-level rulesets need a paid plan). AC re \"no human/admin bypass\" is therefore realized as: no direct/accidental pushes; TRUSTED repo admins CAN deliberately edit/disable the repo-level rule — an explicitly accepted risk for this PoC. (Refines AC4.)\n- Domain: rebar.solutions.navateam.com (Gerrit + MCP on one host, nginx path-routed behind one cert).\n- Infra lives under infra/ in the rebar repo and MUST be excluded from all distribution channels (sdist/wheel/Homebrew/MCP registry).\n- Scope seam with b744: d251 owns the PROVEN PIPE (provision + Gerrit config + replication + lockdown + MCP casting a real LLM-Review vote + infra-level e2e proof). b744-WS6 swaps in the full four-pass reviewer + the real dogfood, plugging into this seam. d251 is independently completable.\n\n== DERISK EXPERIMENTS (real AWS CLI as root + local Docker + gh) ==\n- E1 (S1) AWS readiness: default VPC vpc-01fb22d3dd50a364c exists; AL2023 arm64 AMI via SSM param /aws/service/ami-amazon-linux-latest/al2023-ami-kernel-default-arm64; t4g.large in all us-east-1 AZs; `run-instances --dry-run` of the exact shape (t4g.large/gp3-encrypted/IMDSv2) = \"Request would have succeeded\" (perms + call valid).\n- E2 (S1) DNS: PUBLIC hosted zone solutions.navateam.com EXISTS in this account (Z05558453EZPQLHKC20IQ) -> create rebar.solutions.navateam.com A record there. Critical assumption validated.\n- E3 (S1) Secrets: SSM SecureString put -> get --with-decryption -> delete validated (secrets-at-boot pattern), no lingering param.\n- E4 (S2/S3) Gerrit: official image boots on ARM64 at tag 3.14.1 (bare minor tags 3.14/3.13 DO NOT exist on Docker Hub -> pin a patch tag). Our submit-requirement predicate `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND -has:unresolved` PARSES (HTTP 200) against live Gerrit 3.14.1's query API, as do has:unresolved / -has:unresolved / label:X=MAX. nginx %2F-safe reverse-proxy config (proxy_pass with no path) passes `nginx -t`.\n- E5 (S6) GitHub: navapbc/rebar is public, Issues already off, 0 deploy keys, I have admin; org plan = FREE (repo-level rulesets only). An EXISTING ruleset `main-protection` (id 18048287: pull_request + required_status_checks + deletion + non_fast_forward, admin bypass-via-PR) is INCOMPATIBLE with the mirror lock and must be REPLACED (can't both require human PRs and allow only the deploy key). Ruleset REST payload shape for the DeployKey bypass (actor_id:null, bypass_mode:always; rules update/creation/deletion/non_fast_forward) confirmed against the doc-verified enum.\n\n== ACCEPTED RISKS (on record) ==\nsingle box / no HA; repo-level ruleset editable by trusted repo admins; freeze-on-outage with no break-glass; in-flight reviews lost on a crash (merged code safe on GitHub)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782686374895820001,"uuid":"26f85ec2-a72b-477f-a84a-766e255b0a07"}